{"sectionId":649,"sectionIdLiteral":"649","humanId":"lesson-236","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"I rule my mind, which I alone must rule.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 236"},"annotation":"W-236","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-236\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"649#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"649#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>I have a kingdom I must rule.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"649#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>At times, it does not seem I am its king at all.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"649#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>It seems to triumph over me, and tell me what to think, and what to do and feel.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"649#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>And yet it has been given me to serve whatever purpose I perceive in it.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"649#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>My mind can only serve.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"649#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>Today I give its service to the Holy Spirit to employ as He sees fit.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"649#1:7\"><span class=\"snr\">7</span>I thus direct my mind, which I alone can rule.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"649#1:8\"><span class=\"snr\">8</span>And thus I set it free to do the Will of God.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"649#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"649#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Father, my mind is open to Your Thoughts, and closed today to every thought but Yours.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"649#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>I rule my mind, and offer it to You.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"649#2:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>Accept my gift, for it is Yours to me.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"I have a kingdom I must rule. At times, it does not seem I am its king at all. It seems to triumph over me, and tell me what to think, and what to do and 